snippet.textDisplay: I’m not sure if you know Ari Aster, but my brother and I sat down to watch his student film, Midsommar, and Hereditary. He’s amazing at making a scene, drawing it out to the point where you can feel what the character feels. His main characters have ugly cries we all have had. He’s great at psychological horror. Music, fantastic. Personally, I love those movies. Also, my brother found this out, his work is based around “rubber reality.” Similar to how breaking bad shaped their seasons, you have a put together family or community and have it fall apart to where you think, “How did this movie start? How did it get here?” And he doesn’t do jump scares which is nice, it’s all about subtly.
